review_blob: A sweet beer. The smell is sweet, along with the taste. An apple-ish hint almost. The head is a creme color, and has a pleasing aftertaste on the palate. A little heavy.

Beautiful brownish head with a black-as-tar color to the liquid. Full scent hinting of chocolate and black coffee. Initial taste is slightly alcohol-y but strong and rich. Not overly heavy. Aftertaste is about the same with bitter hints from the large ABV.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Rich, caramel colored head, with toffee and roasted scents. Palate is greeted with a slightly sweet and lovely smooth taste. Aftertastes can be slightly bitter, but nothing irritatingly powerful.
